                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/16687",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The redirector helper does not support null values for the $action parameter; you need to provide the action.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2007-09-14T12:13:57.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2007-09-14T12:13:57.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/23157",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jaka",
                        "name": "jaka",
                        "displayName": "Jaka Jancar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "The problem is exists even if you don't use null.\n\nSay, for example, that you want to redirect to \/default\/index\/index. If you want to write the redirection so it works from other modules also, you will write:\n{code:xml} \n$this->_helper->redirector('index', 'index', 'default');\n{code}\n(as opposed to leaving out the third argument)\n\nThis will cause a redirection to \"\/default\" instead of to \"\/\" (redundant action and controller names get hidden, but the redundant module remains).\n\nPlease change:\n{code:php} \n        if (null === $module) {\n            $module = $request->getModuleName();\n            if ($module == $dispatcher->getDefaultModule()) {\n                $module = '';\n            }\n        }\n{code}\nto:\n{code:xml} \n        if (null === $module) {\n            $module = $request->getModuleName();\n        }\n        if ($module == $dispatcher->getDefaultModule()) {\n            $module = '';\n        }\n{code}\nsince assigning the current module if it's null, and omitting the redundant module name (whether determined automatically or specified explicitly) are two separate actions.\n\nJaka",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=jaka",
                        "name": "jaka",
                        "displayName": "Jaka Jancar",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2008-07-28T13:22:05.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2008-07-28T13:22:05.000+0000"
                },
